Description: TO ALLOW FEDERALLY RECOGNIZED AMERICAN INDIAN AND ALASKA NATIVE TRIBES AND TRIBAL ORGANIZATIONS TO ENTER INTO AN AGREEMENT WITH THE INDIAN HEALTH SERVICE (IHS) TO ASSUME FULL FUNDING AND CONTROL OVER PROGRAMS, SERVICES, FUNCTIONS AND ACTIVITIES (PSFA) (OR PORTIONS THEREOF) THAT THE IHS WOULD OTHERWISE PROVIDE FOR INDIANS BECAUSE OF THEIR STATUS AS INDIANS. SUCH ASSUMPTIONS SHALL BE THROUGH COMPACT AND FUNDING AGREEMENT OR CONSTRUCTION PROJECT AGREEMENT, AS AUTHORIZED TITLE V OF THE INDIAN SELF-DETERMINATION AND EDUCATION ASSISTANCE ACT (ISDEAA), 25 U.S.C 458AAA ET SEQ., AND REGULATIONS AT 42 C.F.R. PART 137.
